t.<br><br>Host of the Elements. Three levels of something. Looks like it might summon multiple elemental pets to come and kick @#%$ for awhile.<br><br>Necro(?):<br><br>Wake the Dead. Three levels of maybe new uber undead pet.<br><br>The above effect might instead be a Rez AA ability for clerics.<br>Ranger: <br><br>Guardian of the Forest. Illusion Black wolf for 8 ticks. does 50%/75%/99% Haste and +100/+120/+140 ATK<br><br>Shaman:<br><br>Virulent Paralysis. 1.2 / 1.6 / 2.0 minute disease-based root.<br><br>Superior Cure (as druid above)<br><br>Bard : <br><br>Boastfull Below. up to 50 point damage and 0 second stun. Might not be an AA but its in the middle of the others and kinda looks like one.<br><br>Beastlord:<br><br>Frenzy of Spirits : 99% Haste and +250 ATK for 8 ticks.<br><br>Hobble of Spirits: adds Hobble of Spirits proc which is a snare proc.<br><br>Paragon of Spirit : 3 levels which adds 100 hp 50 mana / 150 hp 65 mana / 200 hp 80 mana per tick for 6 ticks.<br><br>Spirit Call : Might be 3 levels of AA warder pet. &lt;-- very uncertain <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=96131><B>Tilien Venator</a><BR>60 Druid Thingy<BR><a href=http://www.battlezinc.com/dolamroth/><B>Dol Amroth</a><BR>Rodcet<BR> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usuburbanlife.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SuburbanLife</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Puppy</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#333399>(9/23/02 5:48:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=241.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New on Test: PoP AA abilities</span><hr size=1> I just went to lucy and was wondering what these were, that seems like it might be aa abilities, it could also be